    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Metaphor for B-Ball and V-Ball</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Frances Anderton</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Anderton, Frances</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Pacific Palisades Gymnasium for basketball and volleyball is designed by Stephen Kanner of Kanner Architects for Los Angeles City Department of Recreation and Parks; photo (Currents) (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The new Pacific Palisades Gymnasium for basketball and volleyball was designed by Stephen Kanner of Kanner Architects for the Los Angeles City Department of Recreation and Parks. Gym walls, above, are clad in gray and silver corrugated steel. Bathrooms and offices are contained in a corridor that wraps around the gym inside a wavy wall of glass blocks, right. The oval windows with criss-cross lines are metaphors for ''balls compressing against hard surfaces,'' Mr. Kanner said. Half of the $2 million budget was raised by the community, which has access to the building. The gym is in Palisades Park, off Alma Real Drive.</p>
      </block>
